trend_summary: Over the series, low-rise residential subdivisions gradually infill and expand, especially near the eastern highway interchange and south-central sector, trimming contiguous forest. Commercial roofs emerge beside the main east–west road. Water bodies and road hierarchy remain constant, while overall tree cover shrinks slightly, indicating steady suburban maturation rather than rapid urbanization.
notable_changes: Progressive housing expansion east of the lake and along the highway corridor.
New commercial/warehouse roofs added near the central east–west arterial.
Clearing and fragmentation of forest in the south-central and south-west zones.
Infill of vacant lots within earlier cul-de-sac neighborhoods, raising dwelling density.
Minor upgrade of the southeastern highway interchange and adjacent service roads.
